/* 
  EcoHaven Product Features Schema
  -------------------------------
  Current Schema:
  - id: Unique identifier for the product
  - name: Product name
  - price: Product price (string with currency symbol)
  - des: Short product description
  - img: Product image URL
  - category: Product category
  - stock: Available quantity
  - rating: Customer rating (0-5)
  - material: Primary material used
  - weight: Product weight
  - dimensions: Product dimensions
  - isNew: Whether the product is newly added
  - isFeatured: Whether to feature the product prominently
  
  Firebase Migration Notes:
  ------------------------
  1. When migrating to Firebase Firestore:
     - Use a flat structure with a top-level "products" collection
     - Each product should be a separate document with auto-generated IDs
     - Convert price from string to number and store currency separately
     - Store categories in a separate collection and reference by ID
     - Consider adding subcollections for variants, reviews, etc.
  
  2. Example Firestore structure:
     products/
       ├─ [auto-id]/
       │   ├─ name: "Bamboo Toothbrush"
       │   ├─ price: 8.99
       │   ├─ currency: "USD"
       │   ├─ description: "Eco-friendly and biodegradable..."
       │   ├─ imageUrl: "https://..."
       │   ├─ category: "personal-care"
       │   ├─ stock: 150
       │   └─ ...
  
  3. For real-time updates:
     - Use Firestore onSnapshot listeners in React components
     - Implement proper error handling and loading states
*/

